criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient is able to read and understand the Informed Consent Form and he/she will sign
             the Informed Consent.

          -  Male or female in the age range of 18-85 years.

          -  Body Mass Index >20.

          -  Patient presented with airway obstruction and who are designated to undergo
             intervention

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Chest wall deformity;

          -  Spine deformity (including severe scoliosis or kyphosis);

          -  Hirsutism;

          -  Potentially contagious skin lesion on the back;

          -  Skin lesion that would interfere with sensor placement;

          -  Patient is pregnant;

          -  Cardiac pacemaker or implantable defibrillator;
